ANTHRAX, BOVINE - ISRAEL: (HAZAFON) OIE
***************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 20 Aug 2012
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2012; 25(34) [edited]
http://web.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=12217


Anthrax, Israel
---------------
Information received on and dated 20 Aug 2012 from Dr Nadav Galon, Director, Veterinary Services and Animal Health, Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development, Bet Dagan, Israel

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 8 Aug 2012
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 19 Aug 2012
Report date: 20 Aug 2012
Date submitted to OIE: 20 Aug 2012
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: July 2009
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: suspicion, clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (Qeshet): Qeshet, Golan, Hazafon
Date of start of the outbreak: 8 Aug 2012
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 174 / 8 / 8 / 0 / 0
Affected population: a free ranging herd of 87 cows and 87 calves. 7 animals died in the last 10 days and no diagnosis was established. Samples of a cow, which died later, were found positive to the disease.
Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 4.60 percent / 4.60 percent / 100 percent / 4.60 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: contact with infected area
Epidemiological comments: in 1983 anthrax was diagnosed in the same area. The herd was moved to another area and treated with penicillin.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; no vaccination; treatment of affected animals (penicillin)
Measures to be applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Bacteriology Department, Kimron Veterinary Institute (National laboratory)
Tests and results:
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / bacteriological examination / 19 Aug 2012 / Positive
Cattle / optical microscopy / 19 Aug 2012 / Positive
Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 19 Aug 2012 / Positive

Future reporting:
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

Map of current outbreak location: [unfortunately the icon for the location is overlaid by "Golan Heights". - Mod.MHJ]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The summary of the 2009 OIE report is available at http://web.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=event_summary&this_country_code=ISR&reportid=8240.

This is an area of sporadic but persistent risk. - Mod.MHJ]
